y highlighting the uneven relationships produced by normative articulations of sexual citizenship in a wide range of contexts – in prisons, at Pride House, Pride marches, fetish fairs, and the feminist porn awards – as well as within the laws and regulations governing marriage, hate crimes, citizenship, blood donation, and refugee claims.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBelonging (Social psychology)xPolitical aspectszCanada. 0aQueer theoryzCanada. 0aSexual minoritieszCanada. 0aSocial integrationxPolitical aspectszCanada. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Gay Studies.2bisacsh1 aAwwad, Julian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDegagne, Alexa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDhoot, Sonny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDryden, OmiSoore H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDryden, Omisoore H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFink, Marty, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGentile, Patrizia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKinsman, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLenon, Suzanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLenon, Suzanne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSzegheo-Lang, Naomi De, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrevenen, Kathryn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWahab, Amar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWalcott, Rinaldo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Packa